article.headline: Navy 77, Colgate 64
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Kaleo Kina scored 23 points to lead Navy to a 77-64 win over Colgate on Saturday night. Chris Harris added 17 points for the Midshipmen (19-10, 8-6 Patriot League), while Adam Teague chipped in with 12 points. Navy held a 35-31 lead at halftime, and went on a 9-1 run early in the second half to take a 44-35 lead with 16:33 remaining. A separate 8-0 run later in the half would put Navy up 69-54 after Kina's layup with 3:45 remaining. Ben Jonson scored 16 points to lead the Raiders (9-19, 5-9), while Mike Venezia added 14. Colgate ended their regular season on a five-game losing streak. Navy shot 50 percent from the field (26-for-52), including 44.4 percent from 3-point range (8-for-18). Colgate shot 36.5 percent from the field (19-for-52).
